<concept xmlns:ditaarch="http://dita.oasis-open.org/architecture/2005/" class="- topic/topic concept/concept " ditaarch:DITAArchVersion="1.2" id="pat1443017254201" xml:lang="en-us">
	<title class="- topic/title ">Systematic fault avoidance measures</title>
	<titlealts class="- topic/titlealts ">
		<navtitle class="- topic/navtitle ">Systematic fault avoidance measures</navtitle>
	</titlealts>
	<shortdesc class="- topic/shortdesc ">To avoid systematic faults in designs targeted for safety-related
		applications, IEC 61508-2:2010 contains a number of requirements depending on the expected
		safety integrity level of the safety functions.</shortdesc>
	<prolog class="- topic/prolog ">
		<permissions class="- topic/permissions " view="nonconfidential"/>
	</prolog>
	<conbody class="- topic/body  concept/conbody ">
		<p class="- topic/p ">Because the <ph class="- topic/ph "><keyword class="- topic/keyword "><tm class="- topic/tm " tmtype="reg">Cortex</tm></keyword><keyword class="- topic/keyword ">‑A76</keyword></ph> processor has been developed with no information about the final
			system level safety functions, the assumed safety integrity level for systematic fault
			avoidance measures is SIL 3. </p>

		<p class="- topic/p ">This section includes the following tables:</p>
		<ul class="- topic/ul " id="ul_pfq_wc5_tp">
			<li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "><xref class="- topic/xref " href="#pat1443017254201/table_zdd_b35_tp" type="table">Table 1</xref>. Indication of techniques and measures based on IEC
					61508-2, Table B.1.</p></li>
			<li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "><xref class="- topic/xref " href="#pat1443017254201/table_lxm_kw1_5p" type="table">Table 2</xref>. Indication of techniques and measures based on IEC
					61508-2, Table B.2.</p></li>
			<li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "><xref class="- topic/xref " href="#pat1443017254201/table_aff_cy1_5p" type="table">Table 3</xref>. Indication of techniques and measures based on IEC
					61508-2, Table B.3.</p></li>
			<li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "><xref class="- topic/xref " href="#pat1443017254201/table_vvw_ty1_5p" type="table">Table 4</xref>. Indication of techniques and measures based on IEC
					61508-2, Table B.5.</p></li>
			<li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "><xref class="- topic/xref " href="#pat1443017254201/table_nns_zz1_5p" type="table">Table 5</xref>. Indication of techniques and measures based on IEC
					61508-2, Table F.1.</p></li>
		</ul>
		<note class="- topic/note ">
			<ul class="- topic/ul ">
				<li class="- topic/li ">IEC 61508-2, Table B.4 has been omitted because it is related to
					operation and maintenance phase systematic fault avoidance, which are out of
					scope of the <ph class="- topic/ph "><keyword class="- topic/keyword "><tm class="- topic/tm " tmtype="reg">Cortex</tm></keyword><keyword class="- topic/keyword ">‑A76</keyword></ph> design.</li>
				<li class="- topic/li ">For IEC 61508-2, Table F.1, only techniques and measures
					applicable to design entry are included, because synthesis, test insertion,
					placement, routing, layout generation, and chip manufacturing are not in the
					scope of <ph class="- topic/ph "><keyword class="- topic/keyword "><tm class="- topic/tm " tmtype="reg">Cortex</tm></keyword><keyword class="- topic/keyword ">‑A76</keyword></ph>
					activities for <keyword class="- topic/keyword ">Arm</keyword>. These techniques and measures are the responsibility of the
					system integrator or system developer. </li>
			</ul>
		</note>
		
		<p class="- topic/p ">The ISO 26262:2011 standard requires similar consideration of systematic
			faults for safety-related designs. However, the guidance available within the IEC
			61508:2010, especially for IP designs, is currently more comprehensive. Therefore no
			separate information is included in this section for ISO 26262 measures against
			systematic faults. </p>
		<table class="- topic/table " frame="all" id="table_zdd_b35_tp">
			<title class="- topic/title ">Fault avoidance during specification of system design
				requirements</title>
			<tgroup class="- topic/tgroup " cols="4">
				<colspec class="- topic/colspec " colname="col1" colnum="1" colwidth="3*"/>
				<colspec class="- topic/colspec " colname="col2" colnum="2" colwidth="1*"/>
				<colspec class="- topic/colspec " colname="col3" colnum="3" colwidth="2*"/>
				<colspec class="- topic/colspec " colname="col4" colnum="4" colwidth="10*"/>
				<thead class="- topic/thead ">
					<row class="- topic/row ">
						<entry class="- topic/entry " colname="col1">Method</entry>
						<entry class="- topic/entry " colname="col2">SIL 3</entry>
						<entry class="- topic/entry " colname="col3">Applicable</entry>
						<entry class="- topic/entry " colname="col4">How is this addressed for <ph class="- topic/ph "><keyword class="- topic/keyword "><tm class="- topic/tm " tmtype="reg">Cortex</tm></keyword><keyword class="- topic/keyword ">‑A76</keyword></ph>
							design?</entry>
					</row>
				</thead>
				<tbody class="- topic/tbody ">
					<row class="- topic/row ">
						<entry class="- topic/entry " colname="col1">Use of project management</entry>
						<entry class="- topic/entry " colname="col2">M</entry>
						<entry class="- topic/entry " colname="col3">Yes</entry>
						<entry class="- topic/entry " colname="col4">
							<p class="- topic/p ">Project management with defined project stages, gated
								stage entries, reviews and assessments has been followed for both
								the original <ph class="- topic/ph "><keyword class="- topic/keyword "><tm class="- topic/tm " tmtype="reg">Cortex</tm></keyword><keyword class="- topic/keyword ">‑A76</keyword></ph> development, and the additional activities to
								complete the <ph class="- topic/ph "><keyword class="- topic/keyword "><tm class="- topic/tm " tmtype="reg">Cortex</tm></keyword><keyword class="- topic/keyword ">‑A76</keyword></ph> safety case.</p>
							<note class="- topic/note ">Project management is applied throughout design
								and verification activities. Project management is not separately
								addressed in the later tables.</note>
						</entry>
					</row>
					<row class="- topic/row ">
						<entry class="- topic/entry " colname="col1">Appropriate documentation</entry>
						<entry class="- topic/entry " colname="col2">M</entry>
						<entry class="- topic/entry " colname="col3">Yes</entry>
						<entry class="- topic/entry " colname="col4">
							<p class="- topic/p "><ph class="- topic/ph "><keyword class="- topic/keyword "><tm class="- topic/tm " tmtype="reg">Cortex</tm></keyword><keyword class="- topic/keyword ">‑A76</keyword></ph> documentation has been developed as part of
								the <ph class="- topic/ph "><keyword class="- topic/keyword "><tm class="- topic/tm " tmtype="reg">Cortex</tm></keyword><keyword class="- topic/keyword ">‑A76</keyword></ph> development project, and during the
								additional activities to complete the <ph class="- topic/ph "><keyword class="- topic/keyword "><tm class="- topic/tm " tmtype="reg">Cortex</tm></keyword><keyword class="- topic/keyword ">‑A76</keyword></ph> safety case.</p>
							<p class="- topic/p ">The documentation is split into internal and external
								documents. External documents are available to the system
								integrator.</p>
							<note class="- topic/note ">Documentation is required throughout design and
								verification activities. Documentation is not separately addressed
								in the later tables.</note>
						</entry>
					</row>
					<row class="- topic/row ">
						<entry class="- topic/entry " colname="col1">Safety functions separated from non-safety
							functions</entry>
						<entry class="- topic/entry " colname="col2">HR</entry>
						<entry class="- topic/entry " colname="col3">No</entry>
						<entry class="- topic/entry " colname="col4">Because of the general-purpose nature of the <ph class="- topic/ph "><keyword class="- topic/keyword "><tm class="- topic/tm " tmtype="reg">Cortex</tm></keyword><keyword class="- topic/keyword ">‑A76</keyword></ph>
							processor, there is no clear separation between the fault detection and
							control mechanisms, and normal processing functions of the
							processor.</entry>
					</row>
					<row class="- topic/row ">
						<entry class="- topic/entry " colname="col1">Use of structured specification</entry>
						<entry class="- topic/entry " colname="col2">HR</entry>
						<entry class="- topic/entry " colname="col3">Yes</entry>
						<entry class="- topic/entry " colname="col4"><ph class="- topic/ph ">Structured specification methods have been applied
                for the <ph class="- topic/ph "><keyword class="- topic/keyword "><tm class="- topic/tm " tmtype="reg">Cortex</tm></keyword><keyword class="- topic/keyword ">‑A76</keyword></ph> design, as
                applicable.</ph></entry>
					</row>
					<row class="- topic/row ">
						<entry class="- topic/entry " colname="col1">Formal inspection of the specification</entry>
						<entry class="- topic/entry " colname="col2">HR</entry>
						<entry class="- topic/entry " colname="col3">Yes</entry>
						<entry class="- topic/entry " colname="col4">
							<p class="- topic/p ">Design plans, requirements and specifications, and
								verification plans, requirements and specifications are reviewed
								though formal inspection mechanisms by persons independent from the
								author.</p>
							<p class="- topic/p ">Each review has been separately signed-off by a second independent person.
								The reviews are conducted based on pre-defined review questions,
								which are dependent on the type of artifact being reviewed. </p>
						</entry>
					</row>
					<row class="- topic/row ">
						<entry class="- topic/entry " colname="col1">Use of semi-formal methods</entry>
						<entry class="- topic/entry " colname="col2">HR</entry>
						<entry class="- topic/entry " colname="col3">Yes</entry>
						<entry class="- topic/entry " colname="col4">Semi-formal specification methods, such as functional
							block diagrams and state charts, have been used where
							appropriate.</entry>
					</row>
					<row class="- topic/row ">
						<entry class="- topic/entry " colname="col1">Use of checklists</entry>
						<entry class="- topic/entry " colname="col2">R</entry>
						<entry class="- topic/entry " colname="col3">Yes</entry>
						<entry class="- topic/entry " colname="col4">
							<p class="- topic/p ">Checklists are an essential part of <keyword class="- topic/keyword ">Arm</keyword> IP
								development projects.</p>
							<p class="- topic/p ">Each review and assessment is conducted based on a pre-defined set of
								review or assessment questions, which are tailored for the type of
								artifact being reviewed.</p>
						</entry>
					</row>
					<row class="- topic/row ">
						<entry class="- topic/entry " colname="col1">Use of computer aided specification tools</entry>
						<entry class="- topic/entry " colname="col2">R</entry>
						<entry class="- topic/entry " colname="col3">No</entry>
						<entry class="- topic/entry " colname="col4">No particular computer aided specification tools have
							been used during the <ph class="- topic/ph "><keyword class="- topic/keyword "><tm class="- topic/tm " tmtype="reg">Cortex</tm></keyword><keyword class="- topic/keyword ">‑A76</keyword></ph> development.</entry>
					</row>
					<row class="- topic/row ">
						<entry class="- topic/entry " colname="col1">Use of formal methods</entry>
						<entry class="- topic/entry " colname="col2">R</entry>
						<entry class="- topic/entry " colname="col3">Yes</entry>
						<entry class="- topic/entry " colname="col4">Formal methods have been used to prove specific
							properties of the <ph class="- topic/ph "><keyword class="- topic/keyword "><tm class="- topic/tm " tmtype="reg">Cortex</tm></keyword><keyword class="- topic/keyword ">‑A76</keyword></ph> design. Use of formal proofs has been specified
							as part of the <ph class="- topic/ph "><keyword class="- topic/keyword "><tm class="- topic/tm " tmtype="reg">Cortex</tm></keyword><keyword class="- topic/keyword ">‑A76</keyword></ph> verification strategy.</entry>
					</row>
				</tbody>
			</tgroup>
		</table>
		

		<table class="- topic/table " frame="all" id="table_lxm_kw1_5p">
			<title class="- topic/title ">Fault avoidance during system design and development</title>
			<tgroup class="- topic/tgroup " cols="4">
				<colspec class="- topic/colspec " colname="col1" colnum="1" colwidth="3*"/>
				<colspec class="- topic/colspec " colname="col2" colnum="2" colwidth="1*"/>
				<colspec class="- topic/colspec " colname="col3" colnum="3" colwidth="2*"/>
				<colspec class="- topic/colspec " colname="col4" colnum="4" colwidth="10*"/>
				<thead class="- topic/thead ">
					<row class="- topic/row ">
						<entry class="- topic/entry " colname="col1">Method</entry>
						<entry class="- topic/entry " colname="col2">SIL 3</entry>
						<entry class="- topic/entry " colname="col3">Applicable</entry>
						<entry class="- topic/entry " colname="col4">How is this addressed for <ph class="- topic/ph "><keyword class="- topic/keyword "><tm class="- topic/tm " tmtype="reg">Cortex</tm></keyword><keyword class="- topic/keyword ">‑A76</keyword></ph>
							design? </entry>
					</row>
				</thead>
				<tbody class="- topic/tbody ">
					<row class="- topic/row ">
						<entry class="- topic/entry " colname="col1">Definition and use of guidelines and
							standards</entry>
						<entry class="- topic/entry " colname="col2">M</entry>
						<entry class="- topic/entry " colname="col3">Yes</entry>
						<entry class="- topic/entry " colname="col4">
							<p class="- topic/p "><ph class="- topic/ph "><keyword class="- topic/keyword "><tm class="- topic/tm " tmtype="reg">Cortex</tm></keyword><keyword class="- topic/keyword ">‑A76</keyword></ph> development project has followed <keyword class="- topic/keyword ">Arm</keyword> internal
								guidelines and standards. These include, for example, project
								management guidelines, project reviews and assessment, coding
								guidelines.</p>
						</entry>
					</row>
					<row class="- topic/row ">
						<entry class="- topic/entry " colname="col1">Use of project management</entry>
						<entry class="- topic/entry " colname="col2">M</entry>
						<entry class="- topic/entry " colname="col3">Yes</entry>
						<entry class="- topic/entry " colname="col4">See <xref class="- topic/xref " href="#pat1443017254201/table_zdd_b35_tp" type="table">Table 1</xref>.</entry>
					</row>
					<row class="- topic/row ">
						<entry class="- topic/entry " colname="col1">Appropriate documentation</entry>
						<entry class="- topic/entry " colname="col2">M</entry>
						<entry class="- topic/entry " colname="col3">Yes</entry>
						<entry class="- topic/entry " colname="col4">See <xref class="- topic/xref " href="#pat1443017254201/table_zdd_b35_tp" type="table">Table 1</xref>.</entry>
					</row>
					<row class="- topic/row ">
						<entry class="- topic/entry " colname="col1">Use of structured design</entry>
						<entry class="- topic/entry " colname="col2">HR</entry>
						<entry class="- topic/entry " colname="col3">Yes</entry>
						<entry class="- topic/entry " colname="col4">Structured design methods have been applied for the
								<ph class="- topic/ph "><keyword class="- topic/keyword "><tm class="- topic/tm " tmtype="reg">Cortex</tm></keyword><keyword class="- topic/keyword ">‑A76</keyword></ph> design, with defined modules containing specific parts of the
							required functionality.</entry>
					</row>
					<row class="- topic/row ">
						<entry class="- topic/entry " colname="col1">Appropriate modularization</entry>
						<entry class="- topic/entry " colname="col2">HR</entry>
						<entry class="- topic/entry " colname="col3">Yes</entry>
						<entry class="- topic/entry " colname="col4">
							<p class="- topic/p "><ph class="- topic/ph ">The <ph class="- topic/ph "><keyword class="- topic/keyword "><tm class="- topic/tm " tmtype="reg">Cortex</tm></keyword><keyword class="- topic/keyword ">‑A76</keyword></ph> design has been structured based on required
                functionality.</ph>
							</p>
							<p class="- topic/p ">Design and verification activities have been done
								for the defined units.</p>
						</entry>
					</row>
					<row class="- topic/row ">
						<entry class="- topic/entry " colname="col1">Reuse of well-tried components</entry>
						<entry class="- topic/entry " colname="col2">R</entry>
						<entry class="- topic/entry " colname="col3">Yes</entry>
						<entry class="- topic/entry " colname="col4">The <ph class="- topic/ph "><keyword class="- topic/keyword "><tm class="- topic/tm " tmtype="reg">Cortex</tm></keyword><keyword class="- topic/keyword ">‑A76</keyword></ph> design has reused components from well-tried
							designs, and design principles from other <keyword class="- topic/keyword ">Arm</keyword> designs.</entry>
					</row>
					<row class="- topic/row ">
						<entry class="- topic/entry " colname="col1">Use of semi-formal methods</entry>
						<entry class="- topic/entry " colname="col2">HR</entry>
						<entry class="- topic/entry " colname="col3">Yes</entry>
						<entry class="- topic/entry " colname="col4">See <xref class="- topic/xref " href="#pat1443017254201/table_zdd_b35_tp" type="table">Table 1</xref>.</entry>
					</row>
					<row class="- topic/row ">
						<entry class="- topic/entry " colname="col1">Use of checklists</entry>
						<entry class="- topic/entry " colname="col2">R</entry>
						<entry class="- topic/entry " colname="col3">Yes</entry>
						<entry class="- topic/entry " colname="col4">See <xref class="- topic/xref " href="#pat1443017254201/table_zdd_b35_tp" type="table">Table 1</xref>.</entry>
					</row>
					<row class="- topic/row ">
						<entry class="- topic/entry " colname="col1">Use of computer-aided design tools</entry>
						<entry class="- topic/entry " colname="col2">R</entry>
						<entry class="- topic/entry " colname="col3">Yes</entry>
						<entry class="- topic/entry " colname="col4">Simulation has been used throughout the <ph class="- topic/ph "><keyword class="- topic/keyword "><tm class="- topic/tm " tmtype="reg">Cortex</tm></keyword><keyword class="- topic/keyword ">‑A76</keyword></ph>
							design and verification activities.</entry>
					</row>
					<row class="- topic/row ">
						<entry class="- topic/entry " colname="col1">Inspection of the design</entry>
						<entry class="- topic/entry " colname="col2">R</entry>
						<entry class="- topic/entry " colname="col3">Yes</entry>
						<entry class="- topic/entry " colname="col4">
							<p class="- topic/p ">Each RTL module has undergone a formal review. The
								reviews are done based on pre-defined review questions. The reviewer
								is an independent person from the RTL code author. </p>
							<p class="- topic/p ">A second independent person is required to sign off the inspection
								reviews.</p>
						</entry>
					</row>
					<row class="- topic/row ">
						<entry class="- topic/entry " colname="col1">Use of formal methods</entry>
						<entry class="- topic/entry " colname="col2">R</entry>
						<entry class="- topic/entry " colname="col3">Yes</entry>
						<entry class="- topic/entry " colname="col4">See <xref class="- topic/xref " href="#pat1443017254201/table_zdd_b35_tp" type="table">Table 1</xref>.</entry>
					</row>
				</tbody>
			</tgroup>
		</table>

		
		<table class="- topic/table " frame="all" id="table_aff_cy1_5p">
			<title class="- topic/title ">Fault avoidance during system integration</title>
			<tgroup class="- topic/tgroup " cols="4">
				<colspec class="- topic/colspec " colname="col1" colnum="1" colwidth="3*"/>
				<colspec class="- topic/colspec " colname="col2" colnum="2" colwidth="1*"/>
				<colspec class="- topic/colspec " colname="col3" colnum="3" colwidth="2*"/>
				<colspec class="- topic/colspec " colname="col4" colnum="4" colwidth="10*"/>
				<thead class="- topic/thead ">
					<row class="- topic/row ">
						<entry class="- topic/entry " colname="col1">Method</entry>
						<entry class="- topic/entry " colname="col2">SIL 3</entry>
						<entry class="- topic/entry " colname="col3">Applicable</entry>
						<entry class="- topic/entry " colname="col4">How is this addressed for <ph class="- topic/ph "><keyword class="- topic/keyword "><tm class="- topic/tm " tmtype="reg">Cortex</tm></keyword><keyword class="- topic/keyword ">‑A76</keyword></ph>
							design?</entry>
					</row>
				</thead>
				<tbody class="- topic/tbody ">
					<row class="- topic/row ">
						<entry class="- topic/entry " colname="col1">Use of functional testing</entry>
						<entry class="- topic/entry " colname="col2">M</entry>
						<entry class="- topic/entry " colname="col3">Yes</entry>
						<entry class="- topic/entry " colname="col4">
							<p class="- topic/p ">Functional testing of the <ph class="- topic/ph "><keyword class="- topic/keyword "><tm class="- topic/tm " tmtype="reg">Cortex</tm></keyword><keyword class="- topic/keyword ">‑A76</keyword></ph> has been conducted. The functional testing consists of a
								combination of integration (top-level) and unit level tests. </p>
							<p class="- topic/p ">The test stimuli are either manually generated to
								target particular aspects of the design, or randomly generated with
								specific constraints. </p>
							<p class="- topic/p ">Functional test coverage is automatically recorded
								through the use of defined functional coverage points.</p>
						</entry>
					</row>
					<row class="- topic/row ">
						<entry class="- topic/entry " colname="col1">Use of project management</entry>
						<entry class="- topic/entry " colname="col2">M</entry>
						<entry class="- topic/entry " colname="col3">Yes</entry>
						<entry class="- topic/entry " colname="col4">See <xref class="- topic/xref " href="#pat1443017254201/table_zdd_b35_tp" type="table">Table 1</xref>.</entry>
					</row>
					<row class="- topic/row ">
						<entry class="- topic/entry " colname="col1">Appropriate documentation</entry>
						<entry class="- topic/entry " colname="col2">M</entry>
						<entry class="- topic/entry " colname="col3">Yes</entry>
						<entry class="- topic/entry " colname="col4">See <xref class="- topic/xref " href="#pat1443017254201/table_zdd_b35_tp" type="table">Table 1</xref>.</entry>
					</row>
					<row class="- topic/row ">
						<entry class="- topic/entry " colname="col1">Use of black-box testing</entry>
						<entry class="- topic/entry " colname="col2">R</entry>
						<entry class="- topic/entry " colname="col3">Yes</entry>
						<entry class="- topic/entry " colname="col4">Black-box behavior of <ph class="- topic/ph "><keyword class="- topic/keyword "><tm class="- topic/tm " tmtype="reg">Cortex</tm></keyword><keyword class="- topic/keyword ">‑A76</keyword></ph>
							has been verified through top-level and system testing. </entry>
					</row>
					<row class="- topic/row ">
						<entry class="- topic/entry " colname="col1">Consideration of field experience</entry>
						<entry class="- topic/entry " colname="col2">R</entry>
						<entry class="- topic/entry " colname="col3">No</entry>
						<entry class="- topic/entry " colname="col4">No credit has been taken from field experience for
								<ph class="- topic/ph "><keyword class="- topic/keyword "><tm class="- topic/tm " tmtype="reg">Cortex</tm></keyword><keyword class="- topic/keyword ">‑A76</keyword></ph>.</entry>
					</row>
					<row class="- topic/row ">
						<entry class="- topic/entry " colname="col1">Use of statistical testing</entry>
						<entry class="- topic/entry " colname="col2">R</entry>
						<entry class="- topic/entry " colname="col3">Yes</entry>
						<entry class="- topic/entry " colname="col4">Part of the black-box testing can be considered to be statistical
							testing as defined in IEC 61508-7, clause B.5.3, in the sense that the
							test stimuli/application payloads are typical to the final uses of <ph class="- topic/ph "><keyword class="- topic/keyword "><tm class="- topic/tm " tmtype="reg">Cortex</tm></keyword><keyword class="- topic/keyword ">‑A76</keyword></ph>.</entry>
					</row>
				</tbody>
			</tgroup>
		</table>
		
		<table class="- topic/table " frame="all" id="table_vvw_ty1_5p">
			<title class="- topic/title ">Fault avoidance during system safety validation</title>
			<tgroup class="- topic/tgroup " cols="4">
				<colspec class="- topic/colspec " colname="col1" colnum="1" colwidth="3*"/>
				<colspec class="- topic/colspec " colname="col2" colnum="2" colwidth="1*"/>
				<colspec class="- topic/colspec " colname="col3" colnum="3" colwidth="2*"/>
				<colspec class="- topic/colspec " colname="col4" colnum="4" colwidth="10*"/>
				<thead class="- topic/thead ">
					<row class="- topic/row ">
						<entry class="- topic/entry " colname="col1">Method</entry>
						<entry class="- topic/entry " colname="col2">SIL 3</entry>
						<entry class="- topic/entry " colname="col3">Applicable</entry>
